      "instructions": "Preheat the oven to 400F and place a rack in the middle. Grease a round 8 or 9 cake pan and keep aside. Sift the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.\nIn a bowl, beat together the butter and sugar with a hand mixer till its all fluffy. Add the egg, beat it in and then the vanilla and almond extract and beat just once more. Now mix in the buttermilk and the flour mix alternately to this, starting and ending with the flour mix. Mix with a spatula until just about combined. Add the almond slivers as well and mix once more.\nNow spoon the batter to the greased pan and spread it evenly. Cool in the pan for a few minutes and invert on to a cooling rack. Slice and enjoy with your tea!",
